Development of strategic thought in historical perspective. The emphasis is on strategic analysis, its various methods (SWOT analysis, portfolio analysis, competition analysis, etc.) and the possibilities of their use and related problems in personal brand-based business. The most common modern management theories, concepts and business models are also covered. During the course, attention is paid to the practical issues of strategic management and brand management and industry-specific trends.Objectives/eesmärkid:  The aim of the subject is to improve and develop knowledge and skills of the basic concepts and methods of strategic management of personal brand-based business.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  Upon the completion of the course the student: 1) uses the basic concepts of strategic management and understands the theoretical and practical issues of the company's strategic management; 2) understands the specifics of business based on a personal brand and knows how to create business models based on it; 3) analyzes the strategic management of the organization (company) and creates a new strategy based on it; 4) carries out a strategic analysis of the company and its environment in order to critically assess the risks of the business model and the suitability of competitive strategies; 5) knows personal brand-based business trends and can use them in service development.
